<TITLE> 3 of a family, another die in Ctg road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong,May29 (bdnews24.com)Four people including three from a family were killed and one was injured as a car and a bus collided head-on at Chunutia of Lohagora Upazila in Chittagong on Friday morning. The deceased were identified as Khaleda Begum, 55, her daughter Nishat Sharmin 30, Nishat's seven-month old daughter Meherin, and car driver Nurul Amin, 40. Khaleda's husband, critically injured Monjur Ahmed Chowdhury was admitted at Chittagong Medical College Hospital. The niece of Khaleda, Faisal confirmed to bdnews24.com the accident. "The private car heading for Lohagora from Patia collided head-on with a Hanif Paribahan bus coming from opposite direction around 11:30am." Lohagora police chief Anisul Haq Mridha said that two were killed on the spot while other two died on the way to hospital. He said legal action was being taken. bdnews
